column1: # Data Set: These data were collected during the 2015 National Honey Bee Survey in Vermont by Samantha Alger and Alex Burnham with all molecular work being done by the Beltsville lab in Maryland.
# Data Source: 2015 Vermont National Honey Bee Survey
# Funding Source: United States Department of Agriculture (USDA)
# Data Collection: Collection methods are stipulated by the National Honey Bee Survey
# Columns: (from left to right) Beekeeper last name
column2: each virus has a 3 to 4 letter abbreviation followed by (PA=presence/absence) or (CPB=genome copies per bee) VarroaTHR_PA is binary and consists of presence/absence above the threshold.

column1: # Rows: Data points for all columns in order from each collection event
